title: ConnectionService: Send broadcasts with connection results
message:
ConnectionService: Send broadcasts with connection results

This change allows users to define their own actions to perform after connecting to or disconnecting from one of the supported networks. These broadcasts can be received by automation tools like Tasker.

List of added Intents:
1. "pw.thedrhax.mosmetro.event.CONNECTED"
2. "pw.thedrhax.mosmetro.event.DISCONNECTED"

List of Extras:
1. (String) "SSID"
2. (String) "PROVIDER" (see Provider.getName())

* Do not use SSID to choose the algorithm
* Pipeline-like algorithms
    * Easy progress reporting (no mode onProgressUpdate calls)
    * Easy process interrupts (no more if(stopped) checks)
    * Get rid of these giant connect() methods
    * Communication between steps based on HashMap
* Simplified shortcuts
    * Background connection (basic and forced)
    * DebugActivity shortcut
    * Minimalistic shortcut creation dialog

Double check of connectivity doesn't work good on some devices. Also it is not needed anymore, because connection retries are staying here.

title: Release 1.4-19
message: Release 1.4-19

title: Authenticator: Update connection sequence (fixes #10)
message:
Authenticator: Update connection sequence (fixes #10)

* Authenticator now uses Jsoup library to parse server responses (much better than regular expressions)
* Added support for the latest algorithm

message: NetworkReceiver: Fix NullPointerException while turning off Wi-Fi if device was connected to MosMetro_Free

message: Authenticator: Remove unnecessary log messages

title: Register as a browser (only for links ending with "/generate_204") (fixes #7)
message:
Register as a browser (only for links ending with "/generate_204") (fixes #7)

On some devices you can choose which browser to use when connecting to the network through the captive  portal.
If this app is chosen, it will start the DebugActivity and automatically connect to the network.
If the connection was successful, activity will be closed automatically.

title: Authenticator: Check for cycled respone from server (issue #10)
message:
Authenticator: Check for cycled respone from server (issue #10)

Sometimes server doesn't send auth form in it's answer. This change helps to stop algorithm execution when this is happening.

(cherry picked from commit 1c338c8)

title: Authenticator: Remove double setIgnoreSSL() call
message:
Authenticator: Remove double setIgnoreSSL() call
(cherry picked from commit 6e0058c)

title: NetworkReceiver: Try to reconnect to the network if disconnected (fixes #7)
message:
NetworkReceiver: Try to reconnect to the network if disconnected (fixes #7)

New captive portal installed on the network makes Android disconnect from Wi-Fi after 1-2 minutes and it doesn't try to connect again. This option will force reconnect the device to the network immediately.

(cherry picked from commit 9b14059)

message: Release 1.3-18

title: Preferences: Reduce number of tries to 3 and delay between them to 5 seconds.
message:
Preferences: Reduce number of tries to 3 and delay between them to 5 seconds.

If algorithm didn't work from the 3rd try, it probably wouldn't work even from 10th try.

title: Authenticator: Submit the second hidden auth form
message:
Authenticator: Submit the second hidden auth form

It's not always present, but when it is, it should be submitted. So this commit adds second form submitting with all errors ignored.

These changes are ported from the python version of this algorithm: https://github.com/TheDrHax/mosmetro-python/commit/41f6faf6463fe90f98829d7290e027fdb3c1fed7
